32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.5bcf9154-7f9f-4b53-9082-ba045d126756.description=
Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
true - the expression is true
fales - the expression is false
32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.5eaa73ad-37f3-4da5-a51e-c3a8bb013013.prompt=Overwrite file\: 32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.80849e80-f358-4022-9316-f9dc6966d578.description=
Checks to see if a path is an existing file or folder.

Inputs\:
source - The full path path to check. This can be either a local path such as c\:\test.txt, or a unc path such as \\testhost\test.txt. This path is relative to the Windows RAS host that the operation is running on.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for username.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not exist.
success - The operation succeeded.
32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.994c372f-3d60-4143-bf6a-631fc27ce513.description=
FSMove moves a file from one location to another.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file to move.
destination - The destination for the file.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation.
password - Password for the user.
overwrite - If false the operation will fail if Destination exists (true, false).

Responses\:
failure - The move failed.
success - The move succeeded.
32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.a2aa305f-7455-45b2-8fc5-c46e9bdccefe.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.description=
Moves a file to the location specified by alternateStore. If this location is not specified, then the file is deleted. The complete file path is maintained while moving to alternateStore.

Inputs\:
source 	   - The file to move or delete.
alternateStore - The target location of the file.
user	   - The username to use if move to another Windows system.
password	   - The password for the username.
overwrite	   - Overwrite the file if it exists in alternateStore. If set to false and the file exists, the operation will fail.

Responses\:
success - The file is moved or deleted successfully.
failure - There was an error while moving or deleting the file.


32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.e99f0b9a-b130-4d3b-b563-d9fa45184df8.description=
Deletes the file or directory specified.

Input Parameters\:
source - full path to file/directory to be removed (can be a UNC path)
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host while deleting.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
success - The specified path was successfuly removed.
failure - Unable to remove file/directory.


32abc084-cb88-4d54-8a21-39bd28fc2cad.ff52b5cb-fffb-4be1-b70a-4429f334c51a.description=
Creates a directory

Inputs\:
path - the path of the directory to create.
user - The username to use when creating directory.
password - the password for user.

Responses\:
success - directory created
failure - failed to create directory
